This paper deals with natural language processing and specifically with discourse relation classification, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also uses machine learning techniques, such as adversarial networks and domain adaptation, which are commonly used in the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of labeled data, which suggests the possibility of using information retrieval techniques (cs.IR) to improve the classification performance. Finally, the paper uses neural networks, which are a common tool in the sub-category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
